author: @pizzafoot1966
text: Basically a copy of my reply to Graziano Mirata, just more in depth-  Heyyo, are there any API reference for any of these coding languages? Python for myself, but I just want to know what things sent to the Hallite engine do what things.   Will adding _"d {} {} list(beaf_and_cheese)" + whatnot.whatever()_ to the command queue actually do something?  (Obviously not lol, but what _WILL_ do something???)  For example I still don't know what things like this mean.      "t {} {} {}".format(self.id, int(magnitude), round(angle))  This is the thrust()'s return value in the Ship class. Just what does it mean and do?  I was trying to create my own _getShipById()_ function, but ended up just butchering a part of the _planets_ class from the starter bot's entities file to make it work instead.   I kept looking on the Hallite challenge site for API references (in python specifically), trying to figure out what commands added to the command queue do what different things, but I had no luck.
